article.headline: Lipscomb 65, McNeese St. 47
article.story: NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Michael Lusk scored 16 points and Lipscomb started fast for a 65-47 victory Thursday over McNeese State. Lipscomb (3-5) led 31-14 at the half after bolting ahead 16-4 with 12:33 left on a layup by Thomas Pfaff. Brandon Brown added 10 points for Lipscomb and was the only other Bison in double figures. McNeese State (2-3) had just one player in double figures, John Ford with 12. The Bisons hit 10-of-23 3-pointers while McNeese State made just 3-of-15.
